data.title: Radio Broadcasting History, Radio Stations by City (Pittsburgh)
data.text:
WKHB, Pittsburgh - Irwin

JWNote: WKHB is a direct descendant of WHJB Greensburg.

Clarke Ingram reports: In 1999 WHJB changed its calls and

city of license, raised the daytime power, and moved in; it

became much more of a Pittsburgh station, and with 5,500

watts on 620, covers parts of five states in the daytime.

Clarke Ingram
